suffered no such quaking; (3) the island became stable only when Latona arrived to give birth on \softline
it; (4) Apollo later made the wandering island stable out of }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 pietas}{\plain \fs24 \f1  (the version sponsored by \softline
}{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Aeneid}{\plain \fs24 \f1  III.73-77).  Either the third or this last, partly because of its Virgilian authority, seems the \softline
best to follow.  The mountain's wild quaking reminds the poet of the agitated condition of the \softline
floating island, which welcomed Latona for her parturition, before it was made fast, either by her \softline
arrival or, later, by Apollo.\par
